Always smells like urine.

494
00:39:27,543 --> 00:39:30,739
JIMl:
My lyrics, exactly. See, guys. I told you.

495
00:39:30,914 --> 00:39:33,474
PUDGE:
Your lyrics stink worse than the alley.

496
00:39:33,650 --> 00:39:35,550
ISHl: You got it right, dude.
JIMl: Not true.

497
00:39:35,717 --> 00:39:38,710
I write very powerful lyrics.

498
00:39:51,166 --> 00:39:53,157
[MEN LAUGHING]

499
00:39:53,902 --> 00:39:55,199
- Charlie?
- Yeah?

500
00:39:55,371 --> 00:39:57,065
I want you to meet Bobbie Thomas.

501
00:39:57,806 --> 00:40:00,139
Oh, the little girl with the big voice.

502
00:40:00,610 --> 00:40:03,237
Welcome to
the Bobcat Entertainment Company.

503
00:40:03,413 --> 00:40:06,746
Keith, we'll finally see
what kind of manager you are.

504
00:40:07,516 --> 00:40:10,418
Hey, good of you to come.
Gotta run. Thank you.

505
00:40:10,753 --> 00:40:12,050
What just happened in there?

506
00:40:12,487 --> 00:40:16,117
What just happened in there
is I just got you your first record deal.

507
00:40:16,291 --> 00:40:17,519
[ALL LAUGHING]

508
00:40:17,693 --> 00:40:21,130
The train is pulling out and you are on it.

509
00:40:21,931 --> 00:40:24,900
Let's celebrate, you all.
Morita, Sushi House?

510
00:40:25,300 --> 00:40:29,135
<i>Hai.</i> Drinks on the house.

511
00:40:29,304 --> 00:40:31,465
Guys, guys, guys,
I need to talk to Bobbie...

512
00:40:31,641 --> 00:40:33,835
...so, uh, we'll meet you there later.
ISHl: Cool, man.

513
00:40:34,010 --> 00:40:35,943
[BAND CHATTERING]

514
00:40:48,190 --> 00:40:51,318
Let's go, kid. This train is rolling.

515
00:40:54,764 --> 00:40:58,927
When you're ready
for some T-shirts, hats...

516
00:40:59,101 --> 00:41:02,333
...Good Old Boy Merchandise.
That's the place you go.

517
00:41:02,505 --> 00:41:05,099
- We'll call you.
- Keith's a very good guy, by the way.

518
00:41:05,273 --> 00:41:07,639
He'll make you a really good manager.

519
00:41:10,579 --> 00:41:12,514
I thought Mr. Morita was our manager.

520
00:41:14,217 --> 00:41:16,514
Bobbie, Mr. Morita is
a good restaurant manager...

521
00:41:16,686 --> 00:41:17,947
...not a manager of talent.

522
00:41:18,121 --> 00:41:19,782
This is a whole different world.

523
00:41:19,956 --> 00:41:22,447
But he brought us to you,
made the whole thing happen.

524
00:41:23,192 --> 00:41:25,056
He gave me a job
when I really needed it.

525
00:41:26,963 --> 00:41:28,726
It isn't fair.

526
00:41:28,898 --> 00:41:31,889
Now, don't you worry about Morita.
He's being well taken care of.

527
00:41:39,175 --> 00:41:40,938
All right, great. We'll see you then.

528
00:41:41,110 --> 00:41:42,974
MAN: Hey, Keith.
- Hey, buddy, how you doing?

529
00:41:43,146 --> 00:41:44,237
MAN:
Great.

530
00:41:44,414 --> 00:41:46,677
I'd introduce you
but I don't remember his name.

531
00:41:46,849 --> 00:41:48,817
Can't be that important, huh?

532
00:41:48,985 --> 00:41:51,179
- Does that cell call long distance?
- Absolutely.

533
00:41:51,353 --> 00:41:52,719
- You wanna call?
- Could I?

534
00:41:52,889 --> 00:41:54,048
Sure. Dial away.

535
00:41:56,992 --> 00:41:58,983
[PHONE RINGING]

536
00:42:01,963 --> 00:42:03,625
- Hello?
- Aunt Ella, it's me.

537
00:42:03,800 --> 00:42:05,097
<i>I know it's you, child.</i>

538
00:42:05,268 --> 00:42:07,862
No one else would call me at this hour.

539
00:42:08,036 --> 00:42:09,436
It's good to hear your voice.

540
00:42:09,605 --> 00:42:11,731
It's good to hear you too.

541
00:42:11,907 --> 00:42:14,342
Sometimes I get so homesick,
I can hardly stand it.

542
00:42:14,510 --> 00:42:16,000
You can always come home.

543
00:42:16,179 --> 00:42:18,806
I know, but I'm doing pretty good now.

544
00:42:18,981 --> 00:42:22,507
I got a job serving sushi and I met
some guys at work who have a band.

545
00:42:22,684 --> 00:42:24,619
<i>We wrote a song together</i>
<i>about my daddy...</i>

546
00:42:24,786 --> 00:42:26,914
...then Mr. Morita,
who owns the Sushi House...

547
00:42:27,090 --> 00:42:30,422
...and knows everyone in the business,
introduced us to Mr. Haskins...

548
00:42:30,592 --> 00:42:34,393
...who's, like, a really important manager,
and he introduced us to Mr. Bunch...

549
00:42:34,563 --> 00:42:38,090
...who signed us to a recording contract
at Bobcat Entertainment...

550
00:42:38,266 --> 00:42:39,893
...and we're gonna cut a record.

551
00:42:40,068 --> 00:42:42,594
<i>- What do you think?</i>
- I think you need to take a breath.

552
00:42:42,771 --> 00:42:45,400
Heh, I guess I'm just a little excited.

553
00:42:45,574 --> 00:42:46,940
[PHONE BEEPS]

554
00:42:47,110 --> 00:42:49,271
- Your phone's beeping.
- Oh, it's another call.

555
00:42:49,445 --> 00:42:51,913
- Call waiting.
- I gotta go. He's got another call.

556
00:42:52,248 --> 00:42:55,081
- I love you, Ella.
- I love you too, darling.

557
00:42:55,251 --> 00:42:59,244
- Remember, be fair, and...
- Never break a promise, I know.

558
00:42:59,422 --> 00:43:01,253
- Bye, darling.
- Bye.

559
00:43:02,891 --> 00:43:04,483
Hello?

560
00:43:04,659 --> 00:43:07,288
Ha-ha-ha. How you doing, buddy? All right.

561
00:43:07,463 --> 00:43:08,929
I'm good, I'm good.

562
00:43:09,097 --> 00:43:10,588
What about "never tell a lie"?

563
00:43:11,032 --> 00:43:12,465
What?

564
00:43:13,902 --> 00:43:17,463
Well, yeah. Yeah, I've been waiting.

565
00:43:27,382 --> 00:43:29,577
- Leon, how you doing, buddy?
- Good. How are you?

566
00:43:29,751 --> 00:43:31,844
Bobbie, say hi to Leon.
He's your new lawyer.

567
00:43:32,021 --> 00:43:33,681
- Bobbie, Leon. How are you?
- Hi.

568
00:43:33,856 --> 00:43:36,119
- Good to meet you.
- I never had a lawyer before.

569
00:43:36,291 --> 00:43:37,418
Boy, you got one now.

570
00:43:37,592 --> 00:43:42,155
Why don't you two step into the vocal booth
where you can hear yourselves think?

571
00:43:56,445 --> 00:43:58,106
Hey, Charlie.

572
00:43:58,280 --> 00:44:01,512
- You get her John Henry on the contract?
- Leon's doing it right now.

573
00:44:01,684 --> 00:44:04,652
- How's the band?
- Amateur night in Dixie.

574
00:44:05,153 --> 00:44:08,213
Sorry looking bunch. Get rid of them.
They're not the right image.

575
00:44:08,391 --> 00:44:10,449
She's not gonna like it.

576
00:44:11,126 --> 00:44:13,561
CHARLIE: This little girl is gonna be
the home run hitter...

577
00:44:13,728 --> 00:44:16,561
...if we don't screw it up.
Get her a hot band.

578
00:44:19,268 --> 00:44:25,831
Pam, send Tony down
with 2,000 in 20s. For Keith.

579
00:44:28,577 --> 00:44:32,172
All right, you're the hotshot manager.

580
00:44:32,347 --> 00:44:34,338
You make her happy.

581
00:44:43,226 --> 00:44:45,056
LEON:
I can't wait till you're on the road.

582
00:44:45,228 --> 00:44:47,422
It's a pleasure.

583
00:44:47,597 --> 00:44:50,623
- Glad to represent you.
- Thank you.

584
00:44:55,438 --> 00:44:59,931
- How you're doing, darling?
- Great. I think.

585
00:45:01,376 --> 00:45:03,469
Things seem to be happening so fast.

586
00:45:03,646 --> 00:45:04,943
[SIGHS]

587
00:45:05,780 --> 00:45:09,911
Bobbie, this is your very first lesson
in becoming a star.

588
00:45:10,920 --> 00:45:12,911
Making difficult decisions.

589
00:45:13,088 --> 00:45:15,387
And you gotta make one right now.

590
00:45:17,226 --> 00:45:18,693
There's a problem with the band.

591
00:45:19,327 --> 00:45:21,228
What kind of problem? I'll talk to them.

592
00:45:21,396 --> 00:45:23,922
Unfortunately, that won't help.

593
00:45:24,333 --> 00:45:28,235
Truth is, they're just not very good.
We're gonna have to replace them.

594
00:45:33,509 --> 00:45:35,476
But they can get better.

595
00:45:35,644 --> 00:45:38,079
They'll work. I know these guys.
They'll work.

596
00:45:38,246 --> 00:45:40,909
Darling, I would love to be able
to dunk a basketball...

597
00:45:41,083 --> 00:45:43,916
...but no matter how hard I work,
it ain't ever gonna happen.

598
00:45:44,085 --> 00:45:46,748
But it's not fair.
I wouldn't be here without them.

599
00:45:46,922 --> 00:45:49,550
Kid, I'm sorry.
That's the way it's gotta be.

600
00:45:49,724 --> 00:45:52,193
You are the real talent here.

601
00:45:52,360 --> 00:45:54,454
This isn't charity work.
This is the big time.

602
00:45:54,630 --> 00:45:57,690
I know, but maybe we can...

603
00:45:57,867 --> 00:46:00,460
- Hey, is this a bad time?
- No, not at all. Come on in.

604
00:46:00,635 --> 00:46:02,126
Bobbie, Tony, your accountant.

605
00:46:02,304 --> 00:46:05,331
- Hi.
- Brought you a small advance.

606
00:46:05,907 --> 00:46:08,740
- What's this?
- That is just a tiny advance on the money...

607
00:46:08,911 --> 00:46:13,007
...this company knows you're gonna make.
- Shut the front door.

608
00:46:13,916 --> 00:46:15,713
Sign here.

609
00:46:18,219 --> 00:46:22,452
- Thanks. Nice to meet you, Bobbie.
- Nice to meet you, too.

610
00:46:27,329 --> 00:46:30,163
- It isn't fair.
- This is business.

611
00:46:30,333 --> 00:46:32,699
It isn't about being fair.

612
00:46:33,668 --> 00:46:34,693
Are you in?

613
00:46:40,643 --> 00:46:42,371
Yeah, I'm in.

614
00:46:42,545 --> 00:46:43,704
[THUNDER BOOMS]

615
00:46:43,878 --> 00:46:47,679
- Uh-oh. That's two.
- Yes, that's two.

616
00:46:47,849 --> 00:46:49,875
Just one left.

617
00:46:53,054 --> 00:46:56,081
JOSEPH:
Why are we walking? We can fly.

618
00:47:06,735 --> 00:47:08,431
[BAND PLAYING
"WOULD YOU LOVE ME ANYWAY"]

619
00:47:08,603 --> 00:47:13,438
BOBBIE [SINGING]:
<i>Would you love me anyway?</i>

620
00:47:13,608 --> 00:47:20,309
<i>Baby, I need to hear you say</i>

621
00:47:20,483 --> 00:47:22,347
<i>That you know me</i>

622
00:47:22,518 --> 00:47:31,483
You really know me
And you love me anyway

623
00:47:42,704 --> 00:47:44,695
[INAUDIBLE DIALOGUE]

624
00:48:07,096 --> 00:48:09,360
HASKINS:
Why does it need to be a real cowboy?

625
00:48:09,532 --> 00:48:15,027
Because a real cowboy walks, talks,
feels real.

626
00:48:15,204 --> 00:48:18,331
Some model is not gonna be real.

627
00:48:18,507 --> 00:48:20,099
That's ridiculous.

628
00:48:20,275 --> 00:48:24,735
This whole world is an illusion.
Nothing I do is real.

629
00:48:25,347 --> 00:48:26,472
She is.

630
00:48:27,048 --> 00:48:29,608
She's absolutely the real deal.

631
00:48:33,755 --> 00:48:35,746
BOBBIE:
Hey, what about this one?

632
00:48:38,561 --> 00:48:40,358
Let's see.

633
00:48:41,697 --> 00:48:44,860
- He's handsome enough.
- I like him.

634
00:48:45,034 --> 00:48:47,025
- He looks like the real thing.
- Who is he?

635
00:48:47,202 --> 00:48:50,695
Just some cowboy,
rides the rodeo circuit.

636
00:48:50,873 --> 00:48:53,068
A rodeo cowboy.

637
00:48:53,242 --> 00:48:54,902
Perfect.

638
00:49:10,125 --> 00:49:12,422
WOMAN:
Dale, someone's on the phone for you.

639
00:49:12,594 --> 00:49:16,257
- Is it the bank?
- Nope. Some production company.

640
00:49:16,532 --> 00:49:19,056
- Production company?
- Mm-hm.

641
00:49:19,235 --> 00:49:22,329
- What do they want?
- Why don't you talk to them and find out?

642
00:49:22,505 --> 00:49:26,463
- Why don't you not sass me, booper?
- I have to. I'm your sister. It's my job.

643
00:49:26,641 --> 00:49:28,940
- Sure it ain't the bank?
- I'm sure.

644
00:49:29,110 --> 00:49:30,840
- You think it's the bank, Rog?
- Yes.

645
00:49:31,012 --> 00:49:32,001
[LAUGHING]

646
00:49:32,181 --> 00:49:33,739
- Go answer the phone.
- Okay.

647
00:49:35,150 --> 00:49:38,085
I need me a good bull this weekend.

648
00:49:51,467 --> 00:49:52,990
Hello?

649
00:49:55,704 --> 00:49:58,103
Yeah, this is he.

650
00:50:01,809 --> 00:50:03,402
A video?

651
00:50:03,945 --> 00:50:06,972
Yeah. And what would I have to do?

652
00:50:12,320 --> 00:50:14,255
Ride a horse, wear a hat and smile.

653
00:50:14,422 --> 00:50:16,891
Hell, I can do that.

654
00:50:17,226 --> 00:50:19,523
But how much does it pay?

655
00:50:20,329 --> 00:50:22,661
One thousand dollars?

656
00:50:23,398 --> 00:50:25,992
Two thousand dollars?

657
00:50:26,936 --> 00:50:29,097
You gotta be kidding me.

658
00:50:29,737 --> 00:50:33,434
Three thousand dollars?
Shut the front door.

659
00:50:39,614 --> 00:50:41,981
You know who you're talking to?

660
00:50:42,150 --> 00:50:46,280
This is Dale Jordan, the bull rider.

661
00:50:55,469 --> 00:50:57,130
Okay.

662
00:50:57,905 --> 00:50:59,498
Yes, sir.

663
00:51:00,007 --> 00:51:02,306
You got yourself a deal.

664
00:51:07,648 --> 00:51:10,516
You're a hell of a good
negotiator too, sir.

665
00:51:11,286 --> 00:51:12,617
Yes.

666
00:51:13,355 --> 00:51:15,255
See you Monday.

667
00:51:29,204 --> 00:51:33,833
Five thousand dollars.

668
00:51:35,177 --> 00:51:36,576
[SIGHS]

669
00:51:54,128 --> 00:51:55,117
Excuse me, sir.

670
00:51:55,297 --> 00:51:56,286
[HONKS HORN]

671
00:51:57,898 --> 00:52:01,061
I'm Dale Jordan.
Think I'm supposed to be in this deal.

672
00:52:01,235 --> 00:52:04,329
Oh, yeah, the cowboy.
They were just looking for you.

673
00:52:04,505 --> 00:52:08,373
You're in dressing room number two.
Park right next to the dressing room.

674
00:52:08,543 --> 00:52:11,034
Then I think they wanna see you
in the makeup trailer.

675
00:52:11,213 --> 00:52:13,237
Makeup trailer?

676
00:52:13,581 --> 00:52:14,878
Here we go.

677
00:52:15,050 --> 00:52:16,710
What is that stuff you're stirring?

678
00:52:16,885 --> 00:52:22,686
This, my darling, is a special elixir that is
going to have you sparkling like a diamond.

679
00:52:22,858 --> 00:52:27,192
It is my very own personal discovery
of brilliant vitamins and minerals...

680
00:52:27,362 --> 00:52:29,853
...that when applied
to your facial epidermis...

681
00:52:30,032 --> 00:52:35,264
...will make your skin come alive and
dance like angels in front of the camera.

682
00:52:35,436 --> 00:52:38,735
- You're gonna put that on my face?
- No, no, no.

683
00:52:38,907 --> 00:52:41,704
I'm going to paint it, like Picasso.

684
00:52:41,876 --> 00:52:43,606
Now close your eyes.

685
00:52:43,778 --> 00:52:45,576
Come on. Close your eyes.

686
00:52:45,746 --> 00:52:48,375
First, I'm going to take care...

687
00:52:48,550 --> 00:52:51,110
...of this little mustache that's growing
that we're going to...

688
00:52:51,286 --> 00:52:52,684
[CHUCKLING]

689
00:52:53,121 --> 00:52:55,179
Mr. Jordan.

690
00:52:57,893 --> 00:53:01,226
Hi. They're ready for you over in Makeup.

691
00:53:13,240 --> 00:53:17,405
I'm just gonna let this set that
right there.

692
00:53:19,146 --> 00:53:20,478
Wait, wait, wait.

693
00:53:20,648 --> 00:53:23,014
Uh, um...

694
00:53:23,184 --> 00:53:27,052
They sent me here for, uh, like, makeup
or something.

695
00:53:27,222 --> 00:53:29,918
- Oh, oh. The cowboy. Yes, of course.
- Yeah.

696
00:53:30,092 --> 00:53:32,322
All right. Come in, please. Sit down.

697
00:53:32,494 --> 00:53:35,429
- I'll be right with you, all right?
- Okay.

698
00:53:38,467 --> 00:53:41,300
Um, excuse me, one second.

699
00:53:41,469 --> 00:53:44,632
- Hello, are you all right?
- No. I look like an alien pig.

700
00:53:44,806 --> 00:53:46,239
And he saw me.

701
00:53:46,407 --> 00:53:49,536
Oh, come on. Don't be so vain.
You have to come out so I can finish.

702
00:53:49,710 --> 00:53:51,769
I'm not coming out there while he's here.

703
00:53:51,947 --> 00:53:53,346
[CLEARS THROAT]

704
00:53:54,782 --> 00:53:56,273
You know what?

705
00:53:56,451 --> 00:53:59,443
I think we can do you right now.

706
00:54:00,755 --> 00:54:04,851
Hey, I don't want you to put
that white stuff on my face.

707
00:54:05,025 --> 00:54:07,152
Oh, oh. Heaven's no.

708
00:54:07,329 --> 00:54:13,791
With you it's just a matter of a puff there
and a little puff over here.

709
00:54:14,168 --> 00:54:15,726
All right?

710
00:54:16,505 --> 00:54:19,530
I saw that smile.
You can smile, you know.

711
00:54:19,708 --> 00:54:22,438
It's just different for me, okay?

712
00:54:22,610 --> 00:54:26,775
Have a little brush-brush here
and a brush-brush there.

713
00:54:26,947 --> 00:54:29,041
[CHUCKLING]

714
00:54:29,217 --> 00:54:32,744
Okay, here we are, here we are.
Just let me take one look.

715
00:54:35,923 --> 00:54:38,085
You're all done. Okay?

716
00:54:38,260 --> 00:54:39,887
Thank you.

717
00:54:44,532 --> 00:54:46,364
Come out, come out, wherever you are.

718
00:54:46,534 --> 00:54:49,231
- Is he gone?
- Yes, Miss Vain, he's gone.

719
00:54:49,403 --> 00:54:53,135
You can safely emerge
from your place of hiding.

720
00:54:53,340 --> 00:54:54,739
[MAKEUP ARTIST CLEARS THROAT]

721
00:55:01,449 --> 00:55:03,384
What's wrong with my face?

722
00:55:03,552 --> 00:55:05,315
What's wrong with your face?

723
00:55:05,487 --> 00:55:07,614
Nothing's wrong.
You have a beautiful face.

724
00:55:07,789 --> 00:55:11,485
Then why'd you put all this gunk
on my face? You didn't put any on him.

725
00:55:11,927 --> 00:55:17,559
Because, my dear, you are the star.

726
00:55:29,344 --> 00:55:35,976
[SINGING]
<i>We can't trust what we can't see</i>

727
00:55:36,150 --> 00:55:42,282
<i>We're not strong enough to fight</i>
<i>When we feel weak</i>

728
00:55:42,456 --> 00:55:48,918
<i>We can't resist another flame</i>

729
00:55:49,097 --> 00:55:54,864
<i>We're not able to live above the blame</i>

730
00:55:55,402 --> 00:56:01,932
<i>But love is</i>

731
00:56:02,110 --> 00:56:08,048
<i>Love is</i>

732
00:56:08,215 --> 00:56:11,150
