01:13:10,938 --> 01:13:12,302
Smile.

969
01:13:19,979 --> 01:13:21,003
Daddy, you all right?

970
01:13:22,917 --> 01:13:24,612
Daddy?

971
01:13:25,719 --> 01:13:29,654
I've been called about everything else,
but not daddy.

972
01:13:29,823 --> 01:13:31,518
You'll get used to it.

973
01:13:33,761 --> 01:13:35,489
No.

974
01:13:35,996 --> 01:13:38,190
- This isn't any good.
- What do you mean?

975
01:13:38,865 --> 01:13:41,356
This daddy, I'm not a daddy.

976
01:13:41,534 --> 01:13:43,560
Don't say that.

977
01:13:45,405 --> 01:13:49,399
Look, I'm not what you've been dreaming
about all these years.

978
01:13:49,577 --> 01:13:51,203
I'm not a rodeo cowboy.

979
01:13:53,646 --> 01:13:54,671
I'm a drunk.

980
01:13:55,282 --> 01:13:57,978
You asked me what I've been doing.
I've been drinking.

981
01:13:58,319 --> 01:14:02,618
I drink till I pass out,
I drink till I throw up on myself.

982
01:14:03,356 --> 01:14:05,756
I'm no good for you.

983
01:14:05,926 --> 01:14:08,827
Sooner or later, you're gonna get hurt.
I don't wanna hurt you.

984
01:14:10,530 --> 01:14:14,967
The best thing I could do is
go on down the road...

985
01:14:15,135 --> 01:14:16,863
...mind my own business.

986
01:14:17,371 --> 01:14:19,032
You're not going down any road.

987
01:14:21,140 --> 01:14:24,042
I've been waiting my whole life.
I'm not gonna let you just go.

988
01:14:24,511 --> 01:14:25,978
Well, you have to.

989
01:14:29,015 --> 01:14:31,176
I'm an alcoholic.

990
01:14:31,985 --> 01:14:35,386
- I'm sick.
- We'll get you in one of those programs.

991
01:14:35,722 --> 01:14:38,190
I've been through those.
They don't work for me.

992
01:14:38,524 --> 01:14:40,493
But I'm here now.

993
01:14:40,661 --> 01:14:42,492
I'll help you. Whatever it takes.

994
01:14:44,698 --> 01:14:48,997
- We'll get through this together.
- Bobbie, I'm a bad drunk.

995
01:14:49,970 --> 01:14:53,837
A time's gonna come you'll wish to hell
you'd never found me.

996
01:14:56,909 --> 01:15:00,743
Never. I'll be there for you,
no matter what.

997
01:15:02,282 --> 01:15:04,273
I'll be there.

998
01:15:05,019 --> 01:15:06,110
I promise.

999
01:16:06,512 --> 01:16:10,609
MAN 1: Mark, let's do another mic check.
MARK: All right. On my way.

1000
01:16:13,686 --> 01:16:16,917
MAN 1: Hey, double-check those levels.
MAN 2: Got it.

1001
01:16:17,091 --> 01:16:18,489
WOMAN:
Check for the house sound.

1002
01:16:21,828 --> 01:16:25,697
MAN 4: Are they gonna use this spot?
MAN 1: Yes.

1003
01:16:30,203 --> 01:16:32,194
[CREW CHATTERING INDISTINCTLY]

1004
01:16:58,832 --> 01:17:04,030
Hey, check this out.
Come on, come on, watch me, watch me.

1005
01:17:24,323 --> 01:17:26,417
[CROWD CHATTERING]

1006
01:17:27,394 --> 01:17:30,453
How are you?
Me and my best friend right here.

1007
01:17:30,631 --> 01:17:32,655
GUARD:
Come on, Roy, cool off.

1008
01:17:38,805 --> 01:17:40,796
[CATTLE MOOING]

1009
01:17:45,779 --> 01:17:47,747
ANNOUNCER [OVER PA]:
<i>Get the adrenaline pumping...</i>

1010
01:17:47,914 --> 01:17:51,908
<i>... and let's get ready for the bull riding</i>
<i>event of the evening.</i>

1011
01:17:53,220 --> 01:17:55,984
MAN:
Hey, Dale. Good luck, man.

1012
01:17:58,292 --> 01:18:00,020
ANNOUNCER:
<i>Make some noise for this cowboy...</i>

1013
01:18:00,194 --> 01:18:02,957
<i>... because that may be</i>
<i>the only paycheck he gets.</i>

1014
01:18:03,130 --> 01:18:05,462
<i>He's a cowboy that needs to make</i>
<i>a paycheck, folks.</i>

1015
01:18:05,932 --> 01:18:10,063
<i>He's finished number eight all around</i>
<i>and this year he's making a big comeback...</i>

1016
01:18:10,237 --> 01:18:13,434
<i>... after some injuries</i>
<i>he took at Cheyenne last month.</i>

1017
01:18:13,907 --> 01:18:16,375
<i>Cowboy Dale Jordan</i>
<i>was last year's winner...</i>

1018
01:18:16,542 --> 01:18:19,511
<i>... but he's gonna need to score big</i>
<i>to hold the lead.</i>

1019
01:18:19,680 --> 01:18:22,478
MAN:
Get ready. Nice and easy.

1020
01:18:22,649 --> 01:18:25,243
ANNOUNCER:
<i>This bull has been unridden this year.</i>

1021
01:18:25,752 --> 01:18:29,483
<i>He's setting in the chute,</i>
<i>waiting for the nod.</i>

1022
01:18:30,957 --> 01:18:32,948
[BULL MOOING AND SNORTING]

1023
01:18:33,126 --> 01:18:35,117
[CROWD CHEERING]

1024
01:18:45,338 --> 01:18:48,069
ANNOUNCER:
<i>Oh, no. That doesn't look good folks.</i>

1025
01:18:48,242 --> 01:18:51,234
<i>The bullfighters are out there</i>
<i>doing their work.</i>

1026
01:18:52,845 --> 01:18:54,939
Oh, God.

1027
01:18:57,783 --> 01:19:00,184
- Any good news, Bubba?
- Not much.

1028
01:19:00,354 --> 01:19:03,618
- Spurs lost.
- Damn.

1029
01:19:06,993 --> 01:19:08,426
ROY:
All right.

1030
01:19:11,265 --> 01:19:15,667
- Bobbie, tell these rent-a-cops who I am.
- Miss, he keeps saying this is his show.

1031
01:19:15,836 --> 01:19:19,498
- Get the hell out of here. I run this show.
- Stop it. Everyone. Everyone.

1032
01:19:19,672 --> 01:19:21,072
- You shut up.
- Daddy, stop.

1033
01:19:21,240 --> 01:19:22,765
I'll handle this. Shut up!

1034
01:19:22,943 --> 01:19:25,342
- Your daddy?
- Yeah. Come on.

1035
01:19:27,146 --> 01:19:28,478
[GRUNTS]

1036
01:19:34,720 --> 01:19:38,179
- What are you doing?
- Get off me!

1037
01:19:38,358 --> 01:19:41,953
I don't take nothing off nobody,
especially some little snot-nosed kid.

1038
01:19:42,128 --> 01:19:45,292
- What is wrong with you?
- You watch your attitude, you little tramp.

1039
01:19:45,932 --> 01:19:47,695
You're just like your mother.

1040
01:19:47,868 --> 01:19:50,029
All your makeup and a little hussy.

1041
01:19:50,503 --> 01:19:51,561
Get out.

1042
01:19:51,738 --> 01:19:54,069
- Get out of here.
- Nobody tells me what to do.

1043
01:19:54,240 --> 01:19:57,768
- Get out. I never wanna see you again.
- I am not leaving. I like it.

1044
01:19:57,944 --> 01:20:01,141
- There's lots of action, free booze.
- No, you are not staying here.

1045
01:20:01,614 --> 01:20:04,310
- Party time.
- I hate you.

1046
01:20:04,484 --> 01:20:05,746
I wish I'd never found you.

1047
01:20:05,918 --> 01:20:07,146
[THUNDER CRASHES AND ALL GASP]

1048
01:20:07,320 --> 01:20:09,448
Oh, no. No, no, no.

1049
01:20:10,090 --> 01:20:11,579
- That's, um...
- Three.

1050
01:20:11,757 --> 01:20:14,021
...three. Yeah.

1051
01:20:17,229 --> 01:20:18,492
Hey, what's the problem?

1052
01:20:20,067 --> 01:20:21,966
You want some?

1053
01:20:24,070 --> 01:20:25,095
[GRUNTING]

1054
01:20:28,542 --> 01:20:31,533
Hey, Bubba, get his ass out of here.

1055
01:20:32,011 --> 01:20:33,239
Come on, Roy.

1056
01:20:36,082 --> 01:20:37,243
You all right?

1057
01:20:38,251 --> 01:20:39,274
I think so.

1058
01:20:40,052 --> 01:20:41,680
Good, because you got a show to do.

1059
01:20:41,854 --> 01:20:44,516
- You get yourself together.
- I know. I'll be ready.

1060
01:20:44,690 --> 01:20:46,555
Okay. Then let's do it.

1061
01:20:57,671 --> 01:21:02,836
Damn, I think I broke my hand,
that hardheaded SOB.

1062
01:21:03,710 --> 01:21:05,006
[SIGHS]

1063
01:21:10,417 --> 01:21:12,408
[PHONE RINGING]

1064
01:21:16,555 --> 01:21:18,546
[LINE RINGING]

1065
01:22:04,805 --> 01:22:07,273
We're ready for you, Miss Thomas.

1066
01:22:19,618 --> 01:22:21,609
[CROWD CHATTERING]

1067
01:22:43,676 --> 01:22:45,940
[WHIMPERING]

1068
01:22:46,113 --> 01:22:49,047
- Poor little guy.
- It's empty.

1069
01:22:49,216 --> 01:22:52,447
It was a very big voice.
Perhaps too big for her.

1070
01:22:52,618 --> 01:22:55,417
We'll have to put it back on the shelf.

1071
01:23:01,427 --> 01:23:03,453
What was that?

1072
01:23:03,896 --> 01:23:05,421
[CROWD CHEERING]

1073
01:23:05,599 --> 01:23:12,162
ANNOUNCER: <i>Ladies and gentlemen,</i>
<i>Miss Bobbie Thomas.</i>

1074
01:23:12,338 --> 01:23:14,329
[BAND PLAYING COUNTRY SONG]

1075
01:23:26,987 --> 01:23:28,978
[CLEARING THROAT]

1076
01:23:32,024 --> 01:23:34,015
[MUSIC STOPS]

1077
01:23:38,230 --> 01:23:41,597
[CROWD MURMURING]

1078
01:23:41,768 --> 01:23:43,759
[BAND PLAYING COUNTRY SONG]

1079
01:23:50,877 --> 01:23:52,400
[MUSIC STOPS]

1080
01:23:56,850 --> 01:23:58,646
What the...?

1081
01:24:00,319 --> 01:24:02,345
[CROWD JEERING]

1082
01:24:05,391 --> 01:24:07,382
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

1083
01:24:12,032 --> 01:24:15,331
Bobbie, how long have
you been singing?

1084
01:24:15,502 --> 01:24:18,300
My whole life. Why?

1085
01:24:20,207 --> 01:24:21,503
What's wrong with me?

1086
01:24:21,675 --> 01:24:25,405
Well, nothing. Ha.
That's what makes this so unusual.

1087
01:24:25,578 --> 01:24:28,479
We've run every test imaginable,
over and over...

1088
01:24:28,648 --> 01:24:31,082
...and they all say the same thing.

1089
01:24:31,251 --> 01:24:35,051
With your larynx, you should never
have been able to sing at all.

1090
01:24:35,221 --> 01:24:38,088
In simple terms, it's defective.

1091
01:24:38,792 --> 01:24:41,420
- Congenital?
- Since birth.

1092
01:24:41,595 --> 01:24:44,826
HASKINS: What are you saying, doc?
When will she be able to sing again?

1093
01:24:44,997 --> 01:24:47,966
She'll probably never be able
to sing again.

1094
01:24:49,668 --> 01:24:54,128
<i>That's what the voice clinic said, Charlie.</i>
<i>They ran every test possible.</i>

1095
01:24:54,306 --> 01:24:57,673
They don't know how she sung in the
first place. They said it was a miracle.

1096
01:24:57,978 --> 01:25:01,778
Well, maybe it was just a matter of time
before this happened.

1097
01:25:03,850 --> 01:25:06,876
Well, we can't be held responsible
for that.

1098
01:25:07,621 --> 01:25:10,317
The contracts?
Well, of course I have them.

1099
01:25:12,259 --> 01:25:14,658
Of course I read them.

1100
01:25:14,828 --> 01:25:16,819
Oh, you gotta be kidding me.

1101
01:25:16,997 --> 01:25:20,432
Come on, old buddy,
how long we been working together?

1102
01:25:23,737 --> 01:25:26,706
Yeah, well so long to you too.

1103
01:25:36,315 --> 01:25:38,045
Well, kid, I'm sorry.

1104
01:25:38,217 --> 01:25:41,085
If you can't sing,
you're not worth anything in Nashville.

1105
01:25:41,253 --> 01:25:42,720
- What do you mean?
- It's simple.

1106
01:25:42,889 --> 01:25:45,653
You signed the contracts. It's over.

1107
01:25:45,824 --> 01:25:48,055
- What's over?
- Everything's over.

1108
01:25:48,228 --> 01:25:51,560
Your singing career, your record deal...

1109
01:25:51,730 --> 01:25:53,891
...your rented houses, your money,
everything.

1110
01:25:54,067 --> 01:25:55,931
But I've had a number one hit.

1111
01:25:56,101 --> 01:25:59,798
We haven't even released a second single.
There's gotta be some money left.

1112
01:26:00,907 --> 01:26:03,171
Who do you think's paying for all this?

1113
01:26:03,342 --> 01:26:08,177
The cash advance, the studio time...

1114
01:26:08,347 --> 01:26:11,442
...the studio musicians,
the professional band...

1115
01:26:11,618 --> 01:26:14,143
...the producer, the music video...

1116
01:26:14,320 --> 01:26:16,220
...the transportation...

1117
01:26:16,389 --> 01:26:18,448
...Morita's Cadillac...

1118
01:26:18,625 --> 01:26:22,220
...the cell phone bills, everything?
This is part of your deal.

1119
01:26:24,229 --> 01:26:27,596
Right now, you owe the record company
a lot of money.

1120
01:26:27,766 --> 01:26:30,201
And if you're lucky, lucky...

1121
01:26:30,369 --> 01:26:34,305
...your album sales will offset
most of the costs and you won't get sued.

1122
01:26:37,777 --> 01:26:39,608
Singing's what made you special, kid.

1123
01:26:41,480 --> 01:26:44,074
If your voice is gone, so are you.

1124
01:29:09,229 --> 01:29:11,993
I been waiting for you, child.

1125
01:29:22,809 --> 01:29:26,801
I tried to call you a million times.
Why didn't you answer?

1126
01:29:27,313 --> 01:29:30,543
- Are you okay?
- Oh, I'm fine.

1127
01:29:30,984 --> 01:29:33,475
Didn't wanna talk on the phone.

1128
01:29:35,921 --> 01:29:37,650
You look sick.

1129
01:29:38,725 --> 01:29:40,215
You sound sick.

1130
01:29:43,796 --> 01:29:46,162
I lost my voice.

1131
01:29:46,332 --> 01:29:48,027
I know.

1132
01:29:49,469 --> 01:29:52,836
It takes a strong person to carry
a gift that big.

1133
01:29:54,172 --> 01:29:57,073
You have to be strong enough
to follow the rules.

1134
01:29:57,409 --> 01:30:00,277
I don't know what to do if I can't sing.

1135
01:30:00,445 --> 01:30:03,108
You can sing, child. Sing like a bird.

1136
01:30:05,150 --> 01:30:07,813
You just have to learn to do it differently.

1137
01:30:07,987 --> 01:30:09,283
You don't understand.

1138
01:30:10,222 --> 01:30:13,350
I've lost my voice. It's gone.

1139
01:30:14,527 --> 01:30:17,689
And the doctors say I'll never get it back.

1140
01:30:17,863 --> 01:30:21,663
Then you'll have to learn to sing
with your heart.

1141
01:30:26,773 --> 01:30:28,467
How do I do that?

1142
01:30:28,640 --> 01:30:30,939
You search your heart.

1143
01:30:32,211 --> 01:30:33,542
Search for what?

1144
01:30:35,515 --> 01:30:38,244
For a way to make amends.

1145
01:30:38,417 --> 01:30:41,614
For the wrongs that were done
and the people that were hurt.

1146
01:30:44,323 --> 01:30:45,551
Right now...

1147
01:30:46,426 --> 01:30:50,692
...your heart is empty, child. I can feel it.

1148
01:30:52,731 --> 01:30:56,360
When your heart once again is filled...

1149
01:30:56,536 --> 01:30:59,163
...with love and joy...

1150
01:30:59,872 --> 01:31:01,965
...you'll sing again.

1151
01:31:03,976 --> 01:31:08,676
It might not sound the same
but you will sing.

1152
01:31:10,649 --> 01:31:14,211
Sing like you never thought you could.

1153
01:31:35,807 --> 01:31:37,798
[COUNTRY MUSIC PLAYING ON RADIO]

1154
01:31:43,382 --> 01:31:45,408
Sure is nice to see you, again, Bobbie.

1155
01:31:45,585 --> 01:31:47,746
It's nice to see you, too, Wes.

1156
01:31:47,920 --> 01:31:50,649
I appreciate you driving me all this way.

1157
01:31:50,823 --> 01:31:53,552
Aw, what could be better than
a beautiful girl in my truck...

1158
01:31:53,725 --> 01:31:57,217
...driving down the road
on a beautiful afternoon?

1159
01:31:59,265 --> 01:32:01,994
It really is a nice truck.

1160
01:32:27,827 --> 01:32:29,726
- Sure you don't mind waiting?
- No, no.

1161
01:32:29,895 --> 01:32:33,662
Not when I got a CD player
like this baby's got. Ha, ha.

1162
01:32:55,921 --> 01:32:57,582
[SIS CHUCKLES]

1163
01:32:57,756 --> 01:32:59,782
SIS:
Just gentle, like this.

1164
01:33:01,627 --> 01:33:04,390
Hi, I'm Sis. This is Megan.

1165
01:33:04,564 --> 01:33:07,088
Hi, I'm Bobbie.

1166
01:33:07,533 --> 01:33:09,432
I was looking for Dale.

1167
01:33:09,601 --> 01:33:11,399
I know who you are.

1168
01:33:11,570 --> 01:33:15,472
Dale's my brother.
But he isn't here right now.

1169
01:33:16,576 --> 01:33:17,837
[PHONE RINGING]

1170
01:33:18,010 --> 01:33:20,444
Could you stay with Megan
while I go answer the phone?

1171
01:33:20,613 --> 01:33:22,637
- Sure.
- Thanks.

1172
01:33:24,182 --> 01:33:26,047
How you doing, Megan?

1173
01:33:27,185 --> 01:33:29,086
- Do you like horses?
- Yes.

1174
01:33:29,255 --> 01:33:30,483
They're soft.

1175
01:33:31,123 --> 01:33:36,960
They say the softest spot
in the whole world is a horse's nose.

1176
01:33:37,296 --> 01:33:40,060
- Do you wanna feel?
- Mm-hm.

1177
01:33:41,734 --> 01:33:44,259
- You like that?
- Mm-hm.

1178
01:33:49,074 --> 01:33:51,065
[BOBBIE HUMMING]

1179
01:34:20,806 --> 01:34:24,708
Wow. That's amazing.

1180
01:34:25,310 --> 01:34:27,404
Most of the kids will relate to horses...

1181
01:34:27,579 --> 01:34:30,480
...even if they don't pay any attention
to people.

1182
01:34:30,649 --> 01:34:33,083
But we've had trouble with Megan.

1183
01:34:34,554 --> 01:34:38,786
She hasn't responded till now.

1184
01:34:40,359 --> 01:34:42,155
This is amazing.

1185
01:34:42,328 --> 01:34:45,354
Well, this is Dale's thing.

1186
01:34:45,797 --> 01:34:47,731
It's very special.

1187
01:34:48,301 --> 01:34:50,997
That's why he rides all those damn bulls.

1188
01:34:51,170 --> 01:34:54,832
It costs a lot of money
to keep a place like this going.

1189
01:34:57,143 --> 01:35:01,603
I'm not sure what we're gonna do with
him all busted up in the hospital like that.

1190
01:35:01,780 --> 01:35:02,872
Hospital?

1191
01:35:11,524 --> 01:35:12,547
Watch it.

1192
01:35:14,060 --> 01:35:15,856
Oh, sorry.

1193
01:35:22,201 --> 01:35:23,532
Howdy.

1194
01:35:23,703 --> 01:35:25,170
Is he okay?

1195
01:35:25,337 --> 01:35:27,898
Old bull smacked him
pretty good this time.

1196
01:35:28,073 --> 01:35:29,734
I keep telling him he should stop...

1197
01:35:29,908 --> 01:35:34,743
...but he thinks he gotta keep on riding
till that barn's paid off.

1198
01:35:34,913 --> 01:35:38,405
That's his whole deal in life, you know,
helping them kids.

1199
01:35:38,583 --> 01:35:41,712
To look at him, you wouldn't know
he was one of them.

1200
01:35:42,255 --> 01:35:44,314
- What?
- He was autistic like them kids...

1201
01:35:44,489 --> 01:35:45,582
...he's helping now.

1202
01:35:45,757 --> 01:35:47,122
- He was autistic?
- Yep.

1203
01:35:47,292 --> 01:35:50,023
We didn't know
what you called it back then.

1204
01:35:50,195 --> 01:35:51,595
We just thought he was slow.

1205
01:35:51,930 --> 01:35:55,389
Never spoke a word
till he was 11 years old.

1206
01:35:55,568 --> 01:35:59,470
